				<a class="promo_purple" href="#">Get your art portfolio ready</a>
				<a class="promo_purple" href="#">Learn about galleries at Malone</a>
				<!-- /com.omniupdate.div -->
			</div>
			
			<div class="right">
				<!-- com.omniupdate.div label="right" group="Everyone" button="700" -->
				<!-- com.omniupdate.editor csspath="/_resources/ou/editor/maincontent-right.css" cssmenu="/_resources/ou/editor/main.txt" width="950" -->
				<p>The faculty of the Department of Visual Arts is committed to providing all Malone students with educational opportunities designed to stimulate an increasing awareness and interest in art. Because the essence of a culture is reflected in its art, we attempt to enhance cultural awareness through a variety of experiences in the arts. Study in the fine arts should cultivate an appreciation for the arts, encourage participation and employment in the arts, and provide opportunities for the development of the necessary skills for creation and evaluation of specific art forms. Experiences in art are available to both majors and non-majors as essential components of a liberal arts education.</p>
				<p>Nationally known faculty members bring a Christian perspective to the creative process. A variety of emphasis areas are available to students including Painting, Drawing, Fiber Arts, Photography, Ceramics and Graphic Arts. An Art minor is available to students who wish to study art while majoring in other academic areas.</p>
				<p>Opportunities abound for the student artist. Distinctives of our program include a variety of landscapes and architecture that are located within easy access of Malone's campus, offering the student many models to enhance drawing, painting, and photography projects. Students can exhibit their art work in the annual student art exhibit and the annual photo exhibit. The Canton/Akron area is rich with artists working in a variety of media, who regularly visit the classroom to share their expertise or invite students into their studios. Our students enter art work into regional and national exhibits as well.</p>
				<p>We are closely located to the <a href="#">Canton Museum of Art</a>, <a href="#">The Joseph Saxton Gallery</a>, <a href="#">The Massillon Museum</a>, <a href="#">The Akron Museum of Art</a>, <a href="#">The Cleveland Museum of Art</a>, and the <a href="#">Butler Institute of Art</a>.</p>
